---
import Container from '@c/Container.astro';
import Box from '@c/na/Box.astro';
import Em from '@c/Em.astro';
import SectionHeading from './SectionHeading.astro';
---

<section class='pt-[80px] md:pt-[120px] lg:pt-[180px] pb-[80px] md:pb-[120px] lg:pb-[180px] relative bg-black'
        id="one">
        <Container class='mx-auto'>
                <SectionHeading
                        number='4'
                        variant='dark'
                        >One Feedback Solution to Rule Them All</SectionHeading
                >

                <p class='text-brand-grey text-2xl pb-12 tracking-[-0.06rem] lg:text-3xl xl:text-4xl laptop:text-5xl/[1.2]'>
                        With clear pain points and stakeholder requirements, it was easy to mock an <Em variant='dark'>MVP for the developers</Em> to start
                        building. Meanwhile the <Em variant='dark'>Alpha Group and I continued to explore features and refine solutions</Em>. And
                        finally, <Em variant='dark'>I put on my Design System hat and began culling Components and Patterns</Em> weâ€™d need to add to Lumen.
                </p>

                <Box class='body-text text-[#909090] leading-relaxed mb-2.5 md:mb-5 lg:mb-10'>
                        <div class='lg:grid grid-cols-2 lg:mb-10 xl:mb-15 laptop:mb-20'>
                                <div class='p-2 pb-5 order-1 lg:pl-8 xl:pl-12 laptop:pl-15 laptop:pt-8'>
                                        <h3 class='text-brand-pink font-normal lg:pb-2'>Alpha + Beta Community</h3>
                                        <p class='font-normal lg:font-light lg:pb-6 laptop:pb-10'>
                                                Alpha + Beta Community I kicked off an alpha group of 12 power-users to help <Em variant='dark'
                                                        >find corner cases and refine the UX</Em
                                                >
                                                allowing me to design with confidence.
                                        </p>

                                        <p class='font-normal lg:font-light'>
                                                This granted me <Em variant='dark'>more time to focus on design concepts, prototypes, writing spec</Em
                                                > and <Em variant='dark'>designing for less experienced users</Em>. The group was organized and
                                                passionate. We received critical and enthusiastic feedback daily.
                                        </p>
                                </div>

                                <img
                                        src='/img/na/feedback-1.png'
                                        alt=''
                                        class='rounded-lg mb-5'
                                />
                        </div>

                        <div class='lg:grid [grid-template-columns:7fr_8fr]'>
                                <div class='p-2 pb-5 lg:pr-8 xl:pr-12 laptop:pr-15 laptop:pt-10'>
                                        <h3 class='text-brand-pink font-normal lg:pb-2'>In-app Feedback</h3>
                                        <p class='font-normal lg:font-light'>
                                                Being my first time working with a web framework I was quick to suggest <Em variant='dark'
                                                        >embedding an in-app feedback</Em
                                                > tool during late beta. We implemented Appzi and switched to Typeform upon release. In-app feedback lives
                                                in the app to this day acting as the primary touchpoint of user feedback. <Em variant='dark'
                                                        >Many other teams at the company have now adopted this approach.</Em
                                                >
                                        </p>
                                </div>
                                <img
                                        src='/img/na/feedback-2.png'
                                        alt=''
                                        class='rounded-lg mb-1'
                                />
                        </div>
                </Box>

                <Box class='body-text text-[#909090] leading-relaxed'>
                        <div class='p-2 pb-5 lg:pb-10 xl:pb-12 laptop:pb-15'>
                                <h3 class='text-brand-pink font-normal'>User Interviews</h3>
                                <p class='font-normal lg:font-light'>
                                        Solutions to the major pain points were tested and validated during user interviews. We then <Em
                                                variant='dark'>refined upon our solutions, circling back to the same users.</Em
                                        >
                                </p>
                        </div>
                        <iframe
                                src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/nLUw0O05mCM?si=dwvjG0cB4K-CCAQe'
                                title='YouTube video player'
                                frameborder='0'
                                allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share'
                                allowfullscreen
                                class='w-full h-auto aspect-video'
                        ></iframe>
                </Box>
        </Container>
        <section></section>
</section>
